President Obama released a statement mourning the passing of Abner J. Mikva, expressing his gratitude for the influence Mikva had on his own career in public service. Mikva, a former congressman, federal judge, and White House counsel, was a champion for civil liberties and fought against prejudice and discrimination. Obama praised Mikva's integrity and wisdom, noting that he consistently stood on the right side of history. The President also highlighted Mikva's role in empowering the next generation through Mikva Challenge, an organization he established with his wife, Zoe. Obama concluded by offering his condolences to Mikva's family and expressing confidence that Mikva's legacy will continue to inspire Americans to fight for progressive causes.